node.statement: OVERALL CONCLUSION: We have exhaustively analyzed all cases. CASE 1 (g_1(B) = B): CASE 1a (g_2(B) = B): Both subcases (g_3(B) = B and g_3(B) != B) lead to contradiction. CASE 1b (g_2(B) != B): Leads to contradiction via orbit growth analysis. CASE 2 (g_1(B) != B): All subcases lead to contradiction. FINAL RESULT: Our assumption that a non-trivial H-invariant block system exists is FALSE. Therefore, when n + k + m >= 1, the group H = <g_1, g_2, g_3> admits NO non-trivial block system on Omega. QED.
